# Docker set up

```bash
SNEHA@SR MINGW64 ~/Desktop/SB Projects/Patient Management System       
$ cd apigateway


## apigateway image and container create
**SNEHA@SR MINGW64 ~/Desktop/SB Projects/Patient Management System/apigateway** in this directory

### to create the .jar file
```bash
mvn clean package
```

```bash
docker build -t sneharkive/api-gateway .
```

```bash
docker run -d \
  --name api-gateway  \
  --network internal \
  -p 4004:4004 \
  sneharkive/api-gateway
```


# if you made any changes in src folder or any other file or folder that COPY in Dockerfile 
then run inside "SNEHA@SR MINGW64 ~/Desktop/SB Projects/Patient Management System/apigateway (main)" directory

```bash
docker build -t sneharkive/api-gateway .
```

```bash
docker rm -f api-gateway
```

```bash
docker run -d \
  --name api-gateway  \
  --network internal \
  -p 4002:4002 \
  -e SPRING_KAFKA_BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS=kafka:9092 \
  sneharkive/api-gateway
```



## Other commands

### Check Logs (Optional but useful)
Run this to see your Spring Boot logs (helpful to check DB connection, startup, etc.):

```
docker logs -f api-gateway
```


